        <p>April 11, 2015 - The Bulletin | In 2012, veteran David Molina wanted to go to code school, but his GI Bill would not pay his tuition. He tried to teach himself Ruby on Rails, a web development program used to build web applications, but it was just too hard. “I hit a lot of roadblocks,” Molina said. “You shouldn’t have to learn by yourself.” <a href="http://www.bendbulletin.com/localstate/3053094-151/bend-vets-connect-with-operation-code#">Read more...</a></p></br>

