        <p>January 30, 2015 - National Military Examiner | Veterans have been suffering from high unemployment rates for years, but the strategies designed to employee these veterans haven’t changed. The most current numbers were released to media sources in late 2014. Force reduction has hit all branches of the military. The Army alone has plans to reduce its numbers by 200,000 Soldiers, which, no doubt, will lead to increased unemployment for veterans. <a href="http://www.examiner.com/article/operation-code-provides-career-opportunities-for-military-veterans">Read more...</a></p></br>

